# Frontend Conventions

## Stack
Next.js 14 (App Router) · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS · shadcn/ui · React hooks

## UI Theme
**Nautical + Scholarly** dark theme — deep navy background, warm amber/gold accents, Crimson Pro serif headings. Do not introduce new colour variables; use existing Tailwind tokens and CSS vars.

## Directory Layout

```
src/app/              App Router pages (page.tsx, layout.tsx)
src/components/       Feature components (auth/, brain/, upload/, documents/)
src/hooks/            Custom hooks: useAuth, useUpload, useBrain
src/lib/api.ts        Centralised backend HTTP client
src/lib/utils.ts      Shared helpers
```

## API Client Pattern

All backend calls go through `src/lib/api.ts`. Never call `fetch` directly from page components.

```typescript
// ✅ Add new calls in api.ts
export const api = {
  getBrain: () =>
    authFetch('/api/v1/community/brain') as Promise<BrainResponse>,
};

// ✅ Use in a hook or component
const brain = await api.getBrain();
```

When a method is missing from `api.ts`, add it there — don't use inline `fetch` in pages except for one-off admin calls that are explicitly noted.

## Authentication
- Access token → React state only (never `localStorage`)
- Refresh token → httpOnly cookie (managed by backend)
- Use `useAuth` hook to read auth state; never import `AuthContext` directly in leaf components

## State Management
- Local UI state → `useState` / `useReducer`
- Cross-component state → custom hooks with `useContext`
- No external state library needed yet

## Component Patterns

```tsx
// ✅ Named export, typed props
interface BrainStatsProps {
  entities: number;
  relationships: number;
}

export function BrainStats({ entities, relationships }: BrainStatsProps) {
  return (
    <div className="flex gap-4">
      <Stat label="Entities" value={entities} />
      <Stat label="Relationships" value={relationships} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

- Prefer small, focused components over monolithic page files
- Extract reusable pieces into `src/components/`

## Error Handling

```tsx
// ✅ Surface errors explicitly
const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);

try {
  const data = await api.getBrain();
} catch (e) {
  setError('Failed to load brain. Please try again.');
}

{error && <p className="text-destructive text-sm">{error}</p>}
```

## Performance
- Use `React.memo` on pure display components that receive stable props
- Long polling intervals: use `setInterval` inside `useEffect` with cleanup
- Avoid triggering full re-renders of the force-directed graph on unrelated state changes
